// Adversarial: Explode fires on every cell impact (Impacted(Cell)), producing an instant area
// damage burst at the bolt's position. Dense layout means impacts are nearly continuous —
// if Explode entities (or any intermediary damage-dispatch components) aren't cleaned up
// frame-to-frame, NoEntityLeaks fires. High action_prob (0.6) drives rapid breaker movement
// and bumps, ensuring impacts occur from many angles. A chain reaction where Explode damage
// destroys adjacent cells triggering more Explode events is the critical path — if this
// cascade creates unbounded work NoEntityLeaks or NoNaN will surface it.
// Stress: 32 runs to explore diverse impact angles and cascade depths.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.6)),
    max_frames: 8000,
    disallowed_failures: [NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN, BoltInBounds],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 7777,
    initial_effects: [
        On(target: Bolt, then: [
            When(trigger: Impacted(Cell), then: [
                Do(Explode(range: 64.0, damage: 15.0)),
            ]),
        ]),
    ],
)
